Share Dashboards, Widgets, and Lenses

You can share a dashboard, widget, or lens with your colleagues by posting it to Chatter or copying its unique URL. A Chatter post provides an image and a link to the asset in CRM Analytics.

To share:

Click Share.
Click the tab for the sharing method that you want. Post to Feed posts an image and link in Chatter. Export to Quip publishes an image in a new Quip document. Get URL provides a unique URL to the asset.

If posting to Chatter, select User or Group feed, enter the name, and type your comment. You can also remove the image from your post by hovering over it and clicking the X.

If exporting to Quip, click Connect to Quip and then click Publish. Note: After publishing a CRM Analytics snapshot, other Quip users in your org can view the data in the image, including confidential data.

To generate a URL with page and view specifications, either use Get URL or remove the image from Post to Feed by hovering over the image and clicking the X.

If applicable, click Give Access to set the level of sharing access. Click Done.

Required Editions: Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition.

Note: Export to Quip is available in CRM Analytics tabs and embedded CRM Analytics dashboards. The feature isnâ€™t available in the Analytics Studio.
title: Sharing Dashboards, Widgets, and Lenses in Salesforce
